The paper deals with natural language processing and database query generation, which are core topics in the field of computational linguistics (cs.CL) and database systems (cs.DB). The use of pre-training models like BERT and the focus on enhancing schema representation aligns with research in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the evaluation of the proposed method on a benchmark dataset relates to information retrieval (cs.IR).
